<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-239-208 </DOCNO><DOCID>09 834 861</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Jan 22 1991* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>PictureTel unveils low-cost videoconferencing. (System 4000)(product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Buckler, Grant.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   PictureTel Corp. (Product introduction).andO;Ticker:    PCTL.andO;Product:   PictureTel System 4000 (Videoconferencing equipment) (Productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionVideoconferencingCommunications Equipment.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>PICTURETEL UNVEILS LOW-COST VIDEOCONFERENCING  01/22/91 PEABODY,MASSACHUSETTS, U.S.A., 1991 JAN 22 (NB) -- PictureTel Corp., based here,hopes its System 4000 line of dial-up videoconferencing systems will help itsell videoconferencing to companies previously scared off by the cost of thetechnology.andM;PictureTel said the four new compact, modular units priced to open the visualcommunications market beyond the Fortune 500.andP;  The prices start at US$39,500for complete systems, a figure PictureTel said is two-thirds the cost ofexisting videoconferencing offerings.andM;PictureTel said it is able to price the systems lower than their competitionbecause of advanced integration that makes them smaller, more reliable, andeasier to maintain.andP;  PictureTel integrated the formerly separate codec, videoswitcher, audio mixer, network terminal adaptors and audio/video interfaceunit into a PC-sized Electronics Module.andM;Robert F. Mitro, vice-president of sales and marketing, said PictureTelconducted a pilot project in the Chicago area last year, focusing on sellingvideoconferencing to smaller companies, and was &quot;extraordinarily successful.&quot;andM;&quot;Bringing the price down to approximately two thirds of what it was before,while enhancing the capability of the system, we now feel we've got a verystrong entry into the sub-Fortune-500 arena,&quot; he told Newsbytes.andM;PictureTel sees particular promise among legal firms and advertising andpromotional companies, but believes teleconferencing will have appeal to manykinds of businesses, Mitro added.andM;The company also said its System 4000 line delivers the industry's bestpicture and audio quality at data rates from 56 to 768 kilobits per second.andO;The videoconferencing systems are designed to support industry standards,including px64, the company added.andM;PictureTel also reported revenues of US$37.0 million for the calendar year1990, up from US$18.6 million the previous year.andP;  The company had a net lossof US$209,000, compared to a loss of US$4.3 million in 1989.andP;  In the fourthquarter, PictureTel had net income of US$551,000 on revenues of US$11.3million.andM;(Grant Buckler/19910122/Press Contact: Ron Baker, PictureTel, 508-977-9500)</TEXT></DOC>